---
import Layout from "../../../layouts/LayoutDue.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Use"
  description="The terms covering use of the Due app, including reminders, recurring bills, and in-app tips."
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Terms of use</h1>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content">
    <div class="wrap legal-content">
      <span class="legal-updated">Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString("en-US", { year: "numeric", month: "long", day: "numeric" })}</span>

      <h2>Using Due</h2>
      <p>
        Due is provided for personal, non-commercial use on your own iOS device. By downloading or
        using Due, you agree to these terms. If you don't agree with them, please don't use the app.
      </p>

      <h2>Reminders are a convenience, not a guarantee</h2>
      <p>
        Due is designed to help you remember bills before they're due, using dates and reminder
        windows you set yourself. Reminders depend on iOS notification delivery, your device's
        settings, and the accuracy of the information you enter. Due does not guarantee that a
        reminder will be delivered, and is not responsible for late payments, fees, or any other
        consequence of a missed or mistimed reminder. Due is a tool to help you stay organized, the
        responsibility for paying your bills remains yours.
      </p>

      <h2>Your data, your accuracy</h2>
      <p>
        You're responsible for the accuracy of the bill information you enter, names, amounts, due
        dates, and recurrence. Due does not verify this information against any external source,
        because it has no connection to your bank or billers.
      </p>

      <h2>In-app tips</h2>
      <p>
        Due offers optional, one-time tip purchases to support ongoing development. Tips are digital
        goods processed through Apple's App Store and, once completed, are non-refundable except
        where required by law or Apple's own refund policies. Tips do not unlock any feature or
        functionality, every part of Due works identically whether or not you choose to tip.
      </p>

      <h2>No warranty</h2>
      <p>
        Due is provided "as is," without warranty of any kind, express or implied. We don't guarantee
        the app will be error-free, uninterrupted, or fit for any particular purpose beyond what's
        described here.
      </p>

      <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the fullest extent permitted by law, Due and its developer are not liable for any
        indirect, incidental, or consequential damages, including late fees, missed payments, or
        data loss, arising from your use of the app.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
      <p>
        These terms may be updated as the app changes. Continued use of Due after an update means
        you accept the revised terms.
      </p>

      <!-- <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these terms can be sent to <a href="mailto:support@example.com">support@example.com</a>.
      </p> -->
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    background: var(--cream);
    padding: 72px 0 48px;
  }

  .eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--forest);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .page-hero h1 {
    font-size: clamp(30px, 4vw, 42px);
  }

  .content {
    padding: 48px 0 96px;
  }

  .legal-content {
    max-width: 680px;
  }
</style>